<h5>California Residents: Sections 1.1 – 1.9 Detail Your Rights Under the California Consumer Privacy Act</h5>
<b><span>1.1 Sale of Data</span></b>
<p>We may sell your personal information to affiliates or trusted business partners. You have the right to opt-out of the sale of your data to third parties.</p>
<b><span>1.2 Your Privacy Rights</span></b>
<p>If you'd like to review, access, revise or delete personal data we've collected about you, please contact us.</p>
<b><span>1.3 Right to Know</span></b>
<p>You have a right to know what personal data we've collected about you, what data we've sold, who we've sold your data to, and what data we've shared for business purposes.</p>
<b><span>1.4 Right to Access</span></b>
<p>You have the right to see what specific pieces of data we have about you, and to get this data in a portable and easily accessible format.</p>
<b><span>1.5 Right to Delete</span></b>
<p>You have the right to request that we delete your data. We're legally required to keep some data about you, but we'll delete everything we can. Keep in mind that we might reacquire 
some of your data if we purchase data from a third party.</p>
<b><span>1.6 How We Process Your Privacy Rights</span></b>
<p>First we'll verify your identity using your personal info. Then we'll process your request according to company guidelines. You can usually expect a response within 45 days.</p>
<b><span>1.7 Authorized Agent</span></b>
<p>If you're an authorized agent (such as power of attorney) making a request on behalf of someone else, please contact us.</p>
<b><span>1.8 Right to Non-Discrimination For The Exercise Of Your Privacy Rights</span></b>
<p>You won't be discriminated against for exercising your privacy rights.</p>
